Cstrong%3EHarris%20and%20Her%20Indian%20Heritage%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHarris%2C%20half%20Indian%20by%20heritage%2C%20has%20a%20familial%20connection%20to%20Thulasendrapuram%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu.%20Her%20family%20from%20her%20mother's%20side%20come%20from%20there.%20Her%20appointment%20in%202020%20was%20celebrated%20with%20fireworks%20and%20prayers%20in%20India%2C%20with%20Prime%20Minister%20Narendra%20Modi%20calling%20it%20a%20%26quot%3Bhistoric%20occasion%26quot%3B%20and%20expressing%20his%20eagerness%20to%20work%20with%20her%20to%20strengthen%20India-US%20relations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDespite%20the%20initial%20excitement%2C%20it%20is%20clear%20that%20the%20strengthening%20of%20India-US%20relations%20under%20Biden's%20administration%20has%20been%20driven%20by%20the%20President's%20initiatives%20rather%20than%20Harris's%20Indian%20heritage.%20While%20Harris%20often%20speaks%20about%20her%20Indian%20roots%2C%20her%20policies%20and%20actions%20are%20primarily%20shaped%20by%20the%20strategic%20interests%20of%20the%20United%20States%2C%20not%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EThe%20Political%20Strategy%20of%20Indian-Origin%20Politicians%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EA%20few%20Indian-origin%20politicians%20in%20the%20US%2C%20such%20as%20Nikki%20Haley%20and%20Bobby%20Jindal%2C%20tend%20to%20downplay%20their%20Indian%20heritage%20to%20appeal%20to%20broader%20voter%20bases%2C%20which%20can%20be%20seen%20as%20a%20political%20strategy.%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5CnIn%20the%20UK%2C%20Indian-origin%20politicians%20like%20Priti%20Patel%20and%20Suella%20Braverman%2C%20despite%20their%20immigrant%20backgrounds%2C%20have%20adopted%20strict%20anti-immigrant%20stances%2C%20aligning%20with%20conservative%20values%20to%20secure%20support%20within%20their%20parties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ERishi%20Sunak's%20appointment%20as%20the%20UK%20Prime%20Minister%20in%202022%20sparked%20significant%20excitement%20among%20Indians.%20I%20met%20jubilant%20members%20of%20the%20Indian%20community%20in%20Southampton%2C%20Sunak's%20hometown%2C%20who%20felt%20immense%20pride.%20However%2C%20their%20enthusiasm%20later%20dampened%20as%20they%20realised%20that%20Sunak's%20policies%20were%20driven%20by%20the%20priorities%20of%20the%20UK%2C%20not%20his%20Indian%20heritage.%20He%20turned%20out%20to%20be%20just%20another%20politician%20who%20was%20co-opted%20by%20the%20establishment%2C%20they%20felt.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESymbolism%20vs.%20Substance%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20celebrations%20over%20Indian-origin%20politicians%20achieving%20high%20office%20in%20Western%20countries%20often%20overlook%20the%20reality%20that%20these%20leaders%20primarily%20serve%20the%20interests%20of%20their%20respective%20countries.%20For%20instance%2C%20Sunak's%20policies%20were%20guided%20by%20national%20interests%20rather%20than%20ethnic%20connections%2C%20as%20evidenced%20by%20the%20stalled%20Free%20Trade%20Agreement%20(FTA)%20talks%20between%20the%20UK%20and%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESimilar%20cases%20include%20Antonio%20Costa%20and%20Leo%20Varadkar%2C%20former%20Prime%20Ministers%20of%20Portugal%20and%20Ireland%2C%20respectively%2C%20whose%20political%20actions%20did%20not%20necessarily%20favour%20India.%20Costa%2C%20with%20Goan%20roots%2C%20and%20Varadkar%2C%20with%20Maharashtrian%20heritage%2C%20focused%20on%20their%20countries'%20priorities%2C%20not%20their%20ancestral%20ties.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20Indian%20diaspora%2C%20the%20rise%20of%20leaders%20like%20Sunak%2C%20Harris%2C%20Costa%2C%20and%20Varadkar%20is%20a%20source%20of%20inspiration%20and%20pride%2C%20demonstrating%20that%20individuals%20of%20Indian%20descent%20can%20achieve%20the%20highest%20political%20offices%20in%20foreign%20lands.%20However%2C%20the%20tangible%20benefits%20for%20the%20diaspora%20are%20limited.%20For%20example%2C%20the%20Indian%20community%20in%20Southampton%20has%20become%20divided%20over%20whether%20Sunak's%20premiership%20has%20provided%20any%20real%20advantages.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EStarmer's%20Cabinet%20And%20Lack%20Of%20Diversity%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20recent%20UK%20elections%2C%20a%20record%2026%20MPs%20of%20Indian%20origin%20were%20elected%2C%20with%2019%20from%20Labour%2C%20including%2012%20Sikhs%20and%20six%20female%20Sikh%20MPs.%20Despite%20this%20representation%2C%20the%20Indian%20community%20was%20disappointed%20that%20only%20one%20half-Indian%20MP%20received%20a%20senior%20ministerial%20position%20in%20Prime%20Minister%20Keir%20Starmer's%20cabinet.%20This%20cabinet%20appears%20predominantly%20white%2C%20a%20stark%20contrast%20to%20Boris%20Johnson's%20diverse%202019%20cabinet.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Biden%20administration%20has%20appointed%20around%20130%20Indian-Americans%20to%20key%20positions%2C%20reflecting%20the%20growing%20influence%20and%20integration%20of%20Indian-Americans%20in%20US%20politics.%20While%20these%20appointments%20are%20a%20source%20of%20pride%20and%20potentially%20facilitate%20stronger%20India-US%20relations%2C%20the%20primary%20allegiance%20of%20these%20officials%20is%20to%20the%20US.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Indian%20diaspora%20is%20indeed%20an%20influential%20group%20in%20many%20countries%2C%20which%20can%20be%20leveraged%20to%20India's%20advantage.%20That%20explains%20why%20diaspora%20outreach%20is%20one%20of%20PM%20Modi's%20key%20foreign%20policy%20priorities.%C2%A0%3Cbr%3E%5CnThe%20Modi%20government%20has%20also%20been%20advocating%20for%20more%20representations%20for%20India%20at%20influential%20global%20institutions%2C%20such%20as%20the%20International%20Monetary%20Fund%20(IMF)%2C%20the%20World%20Bank%2C%20and%20important%20United%20Nations%20(UN)%20bodies.%20If%20we%20have%20more%20Indians%20or%20Indian-origin%20people%20in%20key%20positions%20in%20these%20institutions%2C%20it%20will%20surely%20bring%20more%20prestige%20and%20power%20to%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EIndian-Origin%20CEOs%20in%20Global%20IT%20Firms%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EApart%20from%20politics%2C%20Indian-origin%20CEOs%20of%20global%20IT%20firms%2C%20such%20as%20Sundar%20Pichai%20of%20Google%20and%20Satya%20Nadella%20of%20Microsoft%2C%20bring%20indirect%20benefits%20to%20India.%20They%20foster%20stronger%20business%20ties%2C%20create%20job%20opportunities%2C%20invest%20in%20Indian%20startups%2C%20and%20promote%20technology%20and%20education%20initiatives.%20Their%20success%20elevates%20India's%20global%20standing%20in%20the%20tech%20world.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThere%20is%20no%20doubt%20that%20the%20achievements%20of%20Indian-origin%20politicians%20and%20business%20leaders%20in%20Western%20countries%20or%20anywhere%20else%20are%20commendable%20and%20a%20source%20of%20pride%2C%20but%20it%20is%20important%20to%20maintain%20a%20realistic%20perspective%20on%20their%20impact.%20Their%20primary%20duty%20is%20to%20serve%20the%20interests%20of%20their%20respective%20countries%2C%20and%20their%20policies%20are%20shaped%20by%20the%20political%20and%20strategic%20priorities%20of%20those%20nations.%20The%20symbolic%20importance%20of%20their%20success%20does%20not%20necessarily%20translate%20into%20tangible%20benefits%20for%20India%20or%20the%20Indian%20diaspora.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20in%20case%20Biden%20withdraws%20from%20the%20race%20and%20Kamala%20Harris%20replaces%20him%20I%20am%20sure%20people%20in%20India%2C%20more%20particularly%20in%20Tamil%20Nadu%2C%20will%20feel%20proud.%20But%20do%20not%20expect%20any%20favours%20from%20her%20if%20she%20wins.%20If%20Trump%20comes%20back%20to%20power%20we%20are%20bound%20to%20remember%20neither%20President%20Biden%20nor%20Kamala%20Harris.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Syed%20Zubair%20Ahmed%20is%20a%20London-based%20senior%20Indian%20journalist%20with%20three%20decades%20of%20experience%20with%20the%20Western%20media)%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EDisclaimer%3A%20These%20are%20the%20personal%20opinions%20of%20the%20author%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%